<P>
   NIGERIA-OPPORTUNITY (Uabuja, Nigeria) _ ``Look, the human rights
here in Nigeria are terrible,'' Theodore Luttwak says, ``but the
opportunities are just fantastic. Tell me, where else in the world
do you have so much money?'' Good question. Abuja, Nigeria's
capital-under-construction, is full of the whiff of oil money, and
not just at the exclusive golf course said to absorb 25 percent of
the city's water supply just to keep the greens smooth. Luttwak _
``just call me Teddy'' _ is out to get his share of the $10 billion
that Nigeria earns each year from oil. By Roger Cohen.
