   BLUE-MAN-APARTMENT (New York) _ Balls of blue paint sail and
splatter. The players catch marshmallows in their mouths and spit
chewed sandwiches onto the stage of the Astor Place Theater in New
York during a typical Blue Man Group performance. It's art as a
kind of graduate-level kindergarten. But when head Blue Man, Chris
Wink, gets home, the scene changes dramatically. Wink, with his
wife Jen Graffam-Wink, a painter, have made their new 800 square
foot apartment in a landmark building on Lafayette Street a
peaceful escape: a holiday from Mr. Wink's work. Call it
light-Blue, like the tones of much of its pacific palette. By
Kimberly Stevens.
