</P>
<P>
   In the third, the Mariners batted around for four runs, plating
them on RBI singles by Alex Rodriguez, Buhner and Davis, and a
run-scoring double by Griffey.
</P>
<P>
   Two innings later, Buhner lunged at a Jaret Wright delivery and
swatted it to right-center for a homer, scoring Edgar Martinez, who
had walked, and David Segui, who had singled. The Mariners now have
a major league-best 162 homers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
