play Pocahontas in John Galliano's fantasy clothes for Dior, which
blend Elizabethan and Indian-maiden themes. Reviews. (slugged:
BC-PARIS-2-(FASHION)-FAIRCHILD)
</P>
<P>
   ``PARIS COUTURE: STARS OF THE EAST.'' From WWD. Japanese
influences played a strong role in the couture collections, as Karl
Lagerfeld displayed them to consummate advantage at Chanel and
Josephus Thimister made them part of a winning show. Reviews.
(slugged: BC-PARIS-3-(FASHION)-FAIRCHILD)
</P>
<P>
   ``PARIS COUTURE: A FAB FINALE.'' From WWD. It was a fine finale
to the fall couture shows, with strong collections from Yves Saint
Laurent, Oscar de la Renta for Balmain and Thierry Mugler. Reviews.
(slugged: BC-PARIS-4-(FASHION)-FAIRCHILD)
</P>
