<P>
   DANCE-SPORT _ PALM BEACH _ Come Sunday, August 2, they will have
danced all week. For the 18th consecutive year, The Triple Crown
DanceSport Championships are waltzing and swinging, mamboing and
boleroing, fox-trotting and quick-stepping their way around the
Gulfstream Ballroom of The Breakers. ``We have about 700 dancers
signed up, and I expect around 1,200 spectators,'' said Larry Dean,
owner of Dance Consultants Unlimited, the event's producer. It's
been accepted as a full exhibition event at the 2000 Olympics in
Sydney, Australia. (Hayes, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
