<P>
   ALZHEIMERS-BOOK _ Mark Warner, an architect and gerontologist
from Jupiter, explains Alzheimer's logic in a new book, ``The
Complete Guide to Alzheimer's-Proofing Your Home,'' published this
month by Purdue University Press, (800) 933-9637. The 470-page book
gives caregivers room-by-room _ and symptom-by-symptom _ advice on
how to make a loved one feel more comfortable and independent at
home. (Fuchs, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
