   LANDFILL-POWER (Albany, N.Y.) _ NEO Corp. of Minneapolis is
mining the Albany dump for methane, a gas that is producing enough
power for 19,000 100-watt light bulbs. Such innovative uses of
garbage are drawing visitors from around the world. By PAUL
GRONDAHL.
</P>
