<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JORDAN-GLANCE-$ADV01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    THE HASHEMITE KINGDOM OF JORDAN
 &HT;    With JORDAN-HUSSEIN-$ADV01.
 &HT;    For Use Saturday, Aug. 1 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By LARRY KAPLOW 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kingdom of Jordan
</P>
<P>
   Geography: About the size of Indiana; bordered by Israel, Syria,
Iraq and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
   Head of state: His Majesty King Hussein Bin Talal; enthroned in
1952.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 4.4 million; about 60 percent are Palestinian, the
remaining 40 percent are Jordanian, Circassian, Armenian and
Bedouin.
</P>
<P>
   Religion: 95 percent Muslim; 5 percent Christian.
</P>
<P>
   Per capita income: $1,528 in 1992.
</P>
<P>
   Language: Arabic.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Aid: Increased dramatically after Jordan signed 1994 peace
treaty with Israel. In 1998, receives $225 million.
</P>
<P>
   Sources: U.S. State Department; Rand McNally World Facts and
Maps; Jordanian government.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
