<P>
   NETWORK _AUSTIN _ A group of more than 140 Austin area
physicians has formed a network to contract for the managed care of
patients in hospitals of St. David's Healthcare Partnership. The
QualityCare Network will give the physicians more leverage in
dealing with health maintenance organizations. The HMOs, often
accused of managing health care costs by limiting care, are
delegating more authority to Austin area primary care and
soecialist doctors who are banding together into so-called
independent physician associations. (Golz, Austin
American-Statesman) ETA: 9 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCHISEFEES _AUSTIN _ Telephone companies press state
regulators for a common franchise fee. As the number of telephone
companies serving communities rises, they don't to negotiate fees
with each municipality. (Hight, Austin American-Statesman) ETA: 9
p.m.
