<P>
   ARCHDEACON _ Dale Earnhardt, the veteran driver and current team
owner was recently rated the sixth most influential person in
NASCAR. Jeff Gordon was rated 10th and they were the only two
active drivers in the TOP 20 list. Earnhardt not only has won seven
driving titles, 71 races and has a huge cadre of fiercly loyal
fans, he is a shrewd business manager whose 1997 income from
various business endorsements was estimated at $19.1 million by
Forbes magagazine. His company, Dale Earnhardt Inc. owns Winston
Cup, Grand National,and NASCAR truck series teams. (Archdeacon,
Dayton Daily News)
</P>
