   FILM-BASEKETBALL &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``BASEketball'' is the type of movie that few people
are going to see once. They'll either avoid it, driven away by
previews and ads that make it look aggressively stupid (which it
often is), or go back for repeat viewings to catch all the dialogue
and cameos they missed the first time _ and eventually rent the
video so they can memorize it. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved
in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-BUFFALO 66 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ How can you not be fascinated with a movie that
features a tap dance musical number staged in a bowling alley?
Especially when it's done by the kittenish Christina Ricci, who
plays the saucer-eyed but loving dimwit kidnapped by Billy Brown
(Vincent Gallo) to impress his folks in ``Buffalo 66.'' By ELVIS
MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-EVER AFTER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Set in 16th-century France, ``Ever After'' is such a
p.c. rendering of the Cinderella story that the stepmother isn't
even evil anymore. She's just snippy. Fortunately, she's played by
Anjelica Huston, who cruises through ``Ever After'' like a slumming
diva; her insouciance is so stylish that the movie achieves a state
of grace when she's onscreen. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
