<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, July 31 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   WELLPOINT-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ WellPoint Health Networks
shares fell 16 percent after the managed health-care company said
it took charges of $108.6 million that resulted in a second-quarter
loss. WellPoint shares fell 10 5/8 to 61 in midmorning trading of
1.38 million, more than four times its three-month daily average,
earlier hitting 60 1/2. California's second-largest health insurer
said it will sell its money-losing workers' compensation unit and
write off an investment in troubled physician-practice manager FPA
Medical Management Inc. By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
